yn Bristowe]]); ''Tonight Show'' Pros & Cons: Going to Marijuana Camp; ''Tonight Show'' Kid Theater (Channing Tatum); X Ambassadors performed \"[[Renegades (X Ambassadors song)|Renegades]]\"\n|LineColor=FF5F57\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=287\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|6|24}}\n|Guests=[[Arnold Schwarzenegger]], [[Mike Birbiglia]]\n|MusicalGuests=[[Major Lazer]] featuring [[M\u00d8 (singer)|M\u00d8]]\n|ShortSummary=Jimmy counts down top/bottom songs in the country; Jimmy calls winner of contest; Brainstorm (Arnold Schwarzenegger); Major Lazer featuring M\u00d8 performed \"[[Lean On]]\"\n|LineColor=FF5F57\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=288\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|6|25}}\n|Guests=[[Mark Wahlberg]], [[Chris Colfer]]\n|MusicalGuests=[[Morrissey]]\n|ShortSummary=[[Bobby Jindal]] Poll Numbers; Jimmy and The Roots tell monologue joke; Hoverboard Tryout Quotes; Cat videos edited with Mitch McConnell hearing; ''Tonight Show'' #hashtags: #EmailFail; ''Tonight Show'' Head Shots (Mark Wahlberg); Morrissey performed \"[[Kiss Me a Lot]]\"\n|LineColor=FF5F57\n}}\n}}\n\n===July===\n{{episode table|overall=4|airdate=17|guests=40|musicalguests=25|background=23EA78|episodes=\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=289\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|7|13}}\n|Guests=[[Paul Rudd]], [[Jon Glaser]]\n|MusicalGuests=[[Echosmith]]\n|ShortSummary=Teachers Union Announcement; Jimmy addresses his hand injury; Drinko (Paul Rudd); Echosmith performed \"Let's Love\"\n|LineColor=23EA78\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=290\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2015|7|14}}\n|Guests=[[LeBron James]], [[Tina Fey]] & [[Amy Poehler]]\n|MusicalGuests=[[OMI (singer)|OMI]]\n|ShortSummary=[[Mark Rivera]] sits in with The Roots; ''Tonight Show'' Pros & Cons: Going to a [[Donald Trump]] Campaign Rally; LeBron James brings Jimmy shoes; Faceketballs (LeBron James); ''Tonight Show'' True Confessions (Tina Fey & Amy Poehler); debut of first trailer for ''[[Sisters (2015 film)|Sisters]]''; O